PetrÃ³l has 3 kombucha Scobies up for grabs for free. Come get it if you wan it!  #fermenteddrinks #scoby #scobyhotel #kombucha #novacancy #overbooked #hotel #takestwototango #petrÃ³lskombutcha #petrÃ³l #istedgade #vesterbro #kÃ¸benhavnThe Palads was established in Copenhagen's former central railway station on Axeltorv which had ceased operations in 1911 following the construction of a new station. After major reconstruction work, the cinema opened on 18 October 1912. With some 3,000 seats and a 30-man orchestra, it was Scandinavia's largest entertainment centre. The former station building was completely demolished in 1917, providing space for today's building designed by Andreas Clemmensen and Johan Nielsen. Kai Nielsen's sculpture of Ursus and the Bull was positioned on the roof from the beginning but was not gilded until 1949.

In 1955, the cinema was comprehensively renovated under the supervision of Holger Pind with new ventilation, carpeting, seating, rosewood wall panneling and the installation of a CinemaScope screen 12 m (39 ft) wide. In the mid-1970s, the cinema suffered from diminishing audiences threatening its viability. Drawing on the experience of the Marignan Concorde cinema in Paris which had been divided up into six auditoriums, the Palads was restructured into 12 auditoriums in 1978. Despite general scepticism, the alterations proved a huge success attracting 57,921 visitors in just one week. In September 1979, a further five auditoriums were opened in the basement. The interior was redecorated throughout in blue and grey with red seating.

In 1989, the outside of the building was painted in vivid pastel colours by Poul Gernes, livening up its appearance, especially when illuminated in the evening. #palads #vesterbro #uniquedanes #cph #danishdesign #danish #livingincph ğŸ¬ğŸ¿ğŸ‡©ğŸ‡°#overhortkobenhavn #overhÃ¸rtikÃ¸benhavn #kÃ¸benhavn #kbh #kbhk #copenhagen #cph #nÃ¸rrebro #vesterbro #Ã¸sterbro #fÃ¦lledparken #parken #humor #sjovt #danskhumor #djÃ¸f #linkedin #tinder #mitkÃ¸benhavn #turistiegenby #visitcopenhagen #venner #visitdenmark #danmark #nÃ¸rrebronx #gotv2dk #andershemmingsendk #sjov #haha#Vesterbro#cph#myhoodHair candy âœ¨

Vi har fÃ¥et en ret fin bikini fra @lovestoriesintimatesğŸŒ¸#es#istedgade110#vesterbro#shopping#nyevarer#bikini#lovestories#ss19In Copenhagen's old quarters, the apartments (which were origianal build to house the ever growing working class in Copenhagen during the big urbanisation in the 1800's) are often so tiny that the residents often choose not to have washing machines eg to achieve more living space.
Instead people use one of the numerous self serviced, public laundries that is scattered around the city. Besides from being a place to do your laundry it's also a very nice place to meet new people, to have cup of coffee from the vending machine or just to read todays newspaper. 
Here is one of the very oldest, which is unfortunately to close soon.
.

I have hardly touched ceramics for a month and i miss it!
I have spend the whole time renovating the new space, packing the old one and moving all my stuff. I had no idea i have so much stuff! I feel kind of rich!
.
My whole body is aching and i am far from finish, BUT next week i will have everything moved into the new studio and the immidiate pressure is over. After that i can take the rest of the renovation and furnishing bit by bit in a more body-attuned tempo, which will be so nice! .
On the photo are two pieces soon on the way to the US - a pitcher and a planter. Handthrown in stoneware and with a mat Snow glaze. Safe journey.Just going to stay here all day â˜ï¸
.
.
.

Sign up: www.butcherslab.dkGYMNASTICS CLASSES: 
WHAT? 
60min classes working on a combination of strength, mobility and skill work. Breaking down common body weight movements such as muscle ups, handstand push ups, toes to bar etc to improve your technique to make you more efficient in the daily WODS. Also through practice, you will learn how to safely scale movements to your level to allow healthy progression. All levels welcome. 
WHEN? 
Mondays at 09:00am 
Thursday at 17:00pm 
HOW? 
Limited spaces, book in via the Butchers Lab app.

Rent: 25.000 DKK
Available: 1/4-2019
Period: 12-60 months
Unfurnished
Case: 201702726

Large bright four-room apartment at the top of the 2nd floor of Scherfig House in the best corner of Carlsberg City with Frederiksberg and Humlebyen as nearest neighbors. The core of the 152 m2 apartment is the huge open living room that combines open kitchen, dining room and living room. With light flowing through from both west and east, from morning to evening, ideal opportunities to enjoy life in the apartment. To the east you can open the doors to your large balcony, which is in direct extension of the living room. Here you can enjoy a warm summer evening and enjoy the sight of the townhouses in the historic Humleby, which is on the other side of the road. To the west, from the living room from both windows and French balcony as well as one of the rooms can enjoy the view over the large, green courtyard, which shares with your neighbors. From the living room there is access to three good rooms of between 10-11 m2. Two of them are located between one of the apartment's two bathrooms and will be ideal if a children's department is needed. All rooms have built-in closets so the space is optimized.

Avoid steam from showers, facials, saunas, and swimming pools, as any excessive moisture will break down the adhesive.
The less you do, the longer your extensions will lastâ€”meaning mascara (especially waterproof kinds), lighten up on the shadow and liner, and ditch the lash curler. Lash curlers, in particular, â€œare very damaging to extensions and can lead to breakage,â€ If you decide to wear any shadow or liner, use an oil-free makeup remover or wipes. Wipe upwards towards your brows instead of down. Basically, you want to avoid getting too close to the lashline.
Pick up some disposable mascara wands for daily cleaning and maintenance. Brush the tops of your lashes to remove any lint or dust. Then, work the brush through from mid-lengths to ends like you would when applying mascara.
If you tend to curl up onto your side when sleeping like I do, just position your head on the pillow so your faceâ€”and lashesâ€”arenâ€™t smushed against it. For about 15 years the former industrial area (meat and slaughtering), has been through a re-programing. Creative minds and service-oriented concepts replace out-dated industry, creating a very popular destination. In an #urbanplanning perspective KÃ¸dbyen is interesting. How will KÃ¸dbyen evolve? Is a development process imminent? 
Sooner or later bigger firms might notice the large customer base KÃ¸dbyen generates and with time replace much of the smaller creative stores and concepts which made the area popular in the first place...sigh. What happens then? Compared to #StrÃ¸get , only the big and wealthy firms can afford the location. Smaller, cooler shops establish themselfs in side alleys integrated with the main pedestrians boulevards. Its also a question about efficiency on valuable urban land. The buildings only have a few floors and massive parking space in between. This contributes to KÃ¸dbyen character and brand, but also means there is money to be made with higher floor-area ratio. I think this might be whats happening at #PapirÃ¸en over on #Christianshavn, not sure. KÃ¸dbyens character could be developed further, but could also dissipate through the urban transformation. Dont know how #KrÃ¸yersplads was prior to transformation, and how much has been kept, but the result seems in line with former use as shipyard and warehouse. Read somewhere about cultural heritage protection and KÃ¸dbyen. Could be  benefitial in continuing KÃ¸dbyens character through urban transformation process. #kÃ¸benhavn #denmark #meatpackingdistrict #vesterbro #urbandesign #cityplanning #architecture #gentrification #byutvikling

Case: 201803385

This beautiful 99 mÂ² apartment offers good location in the hip Vesterbro in Copenhagen.

There are 2 good bedrooms, where there is a possibility to put in a wall so that there are 3 rooms.
A nice living/dining room with large balcony, as well as a bathroom and a kitchen with dishwasher, tumble dryer and washing machine.

The apartment is located in a newer building from 2004.
There is an elevator and private parking for 1000-1200 DKK per person. month.
In addition, the basement room is shared with the landlord.

The apartment is unfurnished, but the landlord has a closet that can be kept or thrown out. In addition, the furniture and parasol will be on the balcony the whole period.

BONUS:
There will be a cool loading bicycle available throughout the rental period.
The apartment is located right next to Copenhagen Central Station and Tivoli Gardens.

For East Asians, the Lunar New Year is a time of reunion. Families around the world will gather together for a New Year Dinner. 
Elaborate food offerings are dedicated to ancestors; Dumplings are folded; the fire for hot pot is set and children spend weeks anticipating their giftâ€”a small red envelope stuffed with money.

Yes, hair rollers are a classic clichÃ© of a 1950s housewife. To me this image stands for so much more. For Caribbean women their hair - or crown - is one of the most important things. Your hair, make-up, nails, dress: all needs to be immaculate. It's something they spend a lot of time on. But Caribbean women also tend to be very efficient. Especially on the island where I was born, CuraÃ§ao, women used to put in their hair rollers in the morning. Then they would do the daily around the house chores, like washing clothes and hanging them up outside. The sun would be a natural hair dryer. In the evening, when it's time to go dancing, you have the perfect hair. My mother used to this. So the image is actually a little homage to my mother â™¥ï¸âœ¨ğŸ‘¸ğŸ½ğŸŒâœ¨
